        }
      ],
      "story": "Kathy's mother grew up in Caracas and went to college there as a teacher. Her father grew u near Paducah, KY. He was working in Venezuela and the Caribbean as the operator of large equipment used to build bridges and harbors, for Raymond International. Kathy was born December 21, 1947 as the first grandchild. Phyliss was born two years later. They moved to Paducah, KY so Kathy and Phyllis could go to school in US. Her father often was working overseas in the Caribbean and Mediterranean. Mimi, Kathy and Phyllis then would join him in the summers. Spain, Morocco and Israel.",
      "title": "Meme",
      "videoUrl": null,
      "year": 1946
    },
